description.narrative:
1. One white paper on poverty reduction developed for discussion and validation during the learning needs assessment workshop, organised jointly with FAO and ITC/ILO
2. One detailed and comprehensive curriculum outline on poverty reduction, including the intertwined and contributing thematic areas, validated by a number of experts from partner institutions, including the UNDP and ITC/ILO;
3. Development of one peer-reviewed and validated lesson content for the e-learning course on poverty reduction, and preparation of materials for the joint UNDP/ITC-ILO/FAO capacity development workshops.

comment.narrative:
1. White paper on poverty reduction developed for discussion and validation during the learning needs assessment workshop, organised jointly with FAO and ITC/ILO, which will include: 
a) the target audience for the curriculum, including their roles and responsibilities (i.e. their job functions);
b) the key job tasks that they should learn or improve to reach the goal of the course; and 
c) the knowledge, skills and competences required to perform the identified tasks;
2. A detailed and comprehensive curriculum outline on poverty reduction, including the intertwined and contributing thematic areas, validated by a number of experts from partner institutions, including the UNDP and ITC/ILO;
3. Development of peer-reviewed and validated lesson content for the e-learning course on poverty reduction, and preparation of materials for the joint UNDP/ITC-ILO/FAO capacity development workshops.
